Pokemon.Name: MissingNo.
Pokemon.Description: It has a sprite that is a strange block of glitched pixels in a backward-L shape. Due to the larger number of characters that can be used to make it appear, it is the most common form.

Pokemon.Name: Bulbasaur
Pokemon.Description: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Ivysaur
Pokemon.Description: There is a plant bulb on its back. When it absorbs nutrients, the bulb is said to blossom into a large flower.

Pokemon.Name: Venusaur
Pokemon.Description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.

Pokemon.Name: Charmander
Pokemon.Description: The flame on its tail indicates Charmander's life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.

Pokemon.Name: Charmeleon
Pokemon.Description: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the air temperature to unbearably high levels.

Pokemon.Name: Charizard
Pokemon.Description: It is said that Charizard's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.

Pokemon.Name: Squirtle
Pokemon.Description: Shoots water at prey while in the water. Withdraws into its shell when in danger.

Pokemon.Name: Wartortle
Pokemon.Description: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

Pokemon.Name: Blastoise
Pokemon.Description: The pressurized water jets on this brutal Pokémon's shell are used for high-speed tackles.

Pokemon.Name: Caterpie
Pokemon.Description: Its feet have suction cups designed to stick to any surface. It tenaciously climbs trees to forage.

Pokemon.Name: Metapod
Pokemon.Description: This Pokémon is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

Pokemon.Name: Butterfree
Pokemon.Description: The wings are protected by rain-repellent dust. As a result, this Pokémon can fly about even in rain.

Pokemon.Name: Weedle
Pokemon.Description: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-coloured body is intended to warn off its enemies.

Pokemon.Name: Kakuna
Pokemon.Description: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

Pokemon.Name: Beedrill
Pokemon.Description: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.

Pokemon.Name: Pidgey
Pokemon.Description: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

Pokemon.Name: Pidgeotto
Pokemon.Description: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

Pokemon.Name: Pidgeot
Pokemon.Description: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.

Pokemon.Name: Rattata
Pokemon.Description: Its fangs are long and very sharp. They grow continuously, so it gnaws on hard things to whittle them down.

Pokemon.Name: Raticate
Pokemon.Description: The webs on its hind legs enable it to cross rivers. It searches wide areas for food.

Pokemon.Name: Spearow
Pokemon.Description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

Pokemon.Name: Fearow
Pokemon.Description: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

Pokemon.Name: Ekans
Pokemon.Description: Moving silently and stealthily, it eats the eggs of birds, such as Pidgey and Spearow, whole.

Pokemon.Name: Arbok
Pokemon.Description: To intimidate foes, it spreads its chest wide and makes eerie sounds by expelling air from its mouth.

Pokemon.Name: Pikachu
Pokemon.Description: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.

Pokemon.Name: Raichu
Pokemon.Description: It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.

Pokemon.Name: Sandshrew
Pokemon.Description: Disliking water, it lives in deep burrows in arid areas. It can roll itself instantly into a ball.

Pokemon.Name: Sandslash
Pokemon.Description: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

Pokemon.Name: Nidoran F
Pokemon.Description: Small and very docile, it protects itself with its small, poisonous horn when attacked.

Pokemon.Name: Nidorina
Pokemon.Description: When feeding its young, it first chews the food into a paste, and then spits it out for the offspring.

Pokemon.Name: Nidoqueen
Pokemon.Description: The body is covered by stiff, needle like scales. If it becomes excited, the needles bristle outwards.

Pokemon.Name: Nidoran M
Pokemon.Description: Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening to distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.

Pokemon.Name: Nidorino
Pokemon.Description: An aggressive Pokémon that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes powerful venom.

Pokemon.Name: Nidoking
Pokemon.Description: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

Pokemon.Name: Clefairy
Pokemon.Description: The moonlight that it stores in the wings on its back apparently gives it the ability to float in midair.

Pokemon.Name: Clefable
Pokemon.Description: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

Pokemon.Name: Vulpix
Pokemon.Description: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

Pokemon.Name: Ninetales
Pokemon.Description: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.

Pokemon.Name: Jigglypuff
Pokemon.Description: If it inflates to sing a lullaby, it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.

Pokemon.Name: Wigglytuff
Pokemon.Description: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

Pokemon.Name: Zubat
Pokemon.Description: It has no eyes. Instead, it relies on its ultrasonic cries for echolocation to flit about in darkness.

Pokemon.Name: Golbat
Pokemon.Description: Once it starts sucking blood, it does not stop until it is full. It flies at night in search of prey.

Pokemon.Name: Oddish
Pokemon.Description: Its scientific name is 'Oddium Wanderus.' At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.

Pokemon.Name: Gloom
Pokemon.Description: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

Pokemon.Name: Vileplume
Pokemon.Description: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

Pokemon.Name: Paras
Pokemon.Description: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

Pokemon.Name: Parasect
Pokemon.Description: The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.

Pokemon.Name: Venonat
Pokemon.Description: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats bugs. It is attracted by light at night.

Pokemon.Name: Venomoth
Pokemon.Description: The wings are covered with dust like scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

Pokemon.Name: Diglett
Pokemon.Description: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light, its blood heats up, causing it to grow weak.

Pokemon.Name: Dugtrio
Pokemon.Description: Extremely powerful, they can dig through even the hardest ground to a depth of over 96 kph.

Pokemon.Name: Meowth
Pokemon.Description: Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

Pokemon.Name: Persian
Pokemon.Description: Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks in an instant.

Pokemon.Name: Psyduck
Pokemon.Description: It has mystical powers but doesn't recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.

Pokemon.Name: Golduck
Pokemon.Description: The forelegs are webbed, helping to make it an adept swimmer. It can be seen swimming elegantly in lakes, etc.

Pokemon.Name: Mankey
Pokemon.Description: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

Pokemon.Name: Primeape
Pokemon.Description: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.

Pokemon.Name: Growlithe
Pokemon.Description: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

Pokemon.Name: Arcanine
Pokemon.Description: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can't help but grovel before it.

Pokemon.Name: Poliwag
Pokemon.Description: The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by area. It is more adept at swimming than walking.

Pokemon.Name: Poliwhirl
Pokemon.Description: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.

Pokemon.Name: Poliwrath
Pokemon.Description: A swimmer adept at both the front crawl and breaststroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

Pokemon.Name: Abra
Pokemon.Description: It senses impending attacks and teleports away to safety before the actual attacks can strike.

Pokemon.Name: Kadabra
Pokemon.Description: If it uses its abilities, it emits special alpha waves that cause machines to malfunction.

Pokemon.Name: Alakazam
Pokemon.Description: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its IQ (intelligence quotient) is said to be around 5,000.

Pokemon.Name: Machop
Pokemon.Description: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

Pokemon.Name: Machoke
Pokemon.Description: It can lift a dump truck with one hand. Using that power, it helps people with heavy jobs.

Pokemon.Name: Machamp
Pokemon.Description: It uses its four powerful arms to pin the limbs of its foe, then throws the victim over the horizon.

Pokemon.Name: Bellsprout
Pokemon.Description: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumoured to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

Pokemon.Name: Weepinbell
Pokemon.Description: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

Pokemon.Name: Victreebel
Pokemon.Description: Once ingested into this Pokémon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

Pokemon.Name: Tentacool
Pokemon.Description: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by their stingers.

Pokemon.Name: Tentacruel
Pokemon.Description: It has 80 tentacles that move about freely. They can sting, causing poisoning and sharp, stabbing pain.

Pokemon.Name: Geodude
Pokemon.Description: It is impossible to distinguish from rocks. It slams against others in contests of hardness.

Pokemon.Name: Graveler
Pokemon.Description: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

Pokemon.Name: Golem
Pokemon.Description: Even dynamite can't harm its hard, boulder-like body. It sheds its hide just once a year.

Pokemon.Name: Ponyta
Pokemon.Description: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parent. It runs in fields and mountains all day.

Pokemon.Name: Rapidash
Pokemon.Description: It gallops at nearly 241 kph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.

Pokemon.Name: Slowpoke
Pokemon.Description: It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail, it won't even notice for a whole day.

Pokemon.Name: Slowbro
Pokemon.Description: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.

Pokemon.Name: Magnemite
Pokemon.Description: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges Thunder Wave and so on from the units at its sides.

Pokemon.Name: Magneton
Pokemon.Description: Generates strange radio signals. It raises the temperature by 2.2 degrees Celsius within 3,300 feet.

Pokemon.Name: Farfetch'd
Pokemon.Description: It always walks about with a plant stalk clamped in its beak. The stalk is used for building its nest.

Pokemon.Name: Doduo
Pokemon.Description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

Pokemon.Name: Dodrio
Pokemon.Description: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.

Pokemon.Name: Seel
Pokemon.Description: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of -40 degrees Celsius.

Pokemon.Name: Dewgong
Pokemon.Description: Its streamlined body has little drag in water. The colder the temperature, the friskier it gets.

Pokemon.Name: Grimer
Pokemon.Description: Appears in filthy areas. It thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

Pokemon.Name: Muk
Pokemon.Description: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.

Pokemon.Name: Shellder
Pokemon.Description: Clamping onto an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.

Pokemon.Name: Cloyster
Pokemon.Description: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

Pokemon.Name: Gastly
Pokemon.Description: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

Pokemon.Name: Haunter
Pokemon.Description: It licks with its gaseous tongue to steal the victim's life force. It lurks in darkness for prey.

Pokemon.Name: Gengar
Pokemon.Description: Hiding in people's shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.

Pokemon.Name: Onix
Pokemon.Description: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 80 kph.

Pokemon.Name: Drowzee
Pokemon.Description: If you think that you had a good dream but you can't remember it, a Drowzee has probably eaten it.

Pokemon.Name: Hypno
Pokemon.Description: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.

Pokemon.Name: Krabby
Pokemon.Description: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

Pokemon.Name: Kingler
Pokemon.Description: Its pincers grow peculiarly large. If it lifts the pincers too fast, it loses its balance and staggers.

Pokemon.Name: Voltorb
Pokemon.Description: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.

Pokemon.Name: Electrode
Pokemon.Description: It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.

Pokemon.Name: Exeggcute
Pokemon.Description: Even though it appears to be eggs of some sort, it was discovered to be a life-form more like plant seeds.

Pokemon.Name: Exeggutor
Pokemon.Description: It is called 'The Walking Jungle'. If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

Pokemon.Name: Cubone
Pokemon.Description: It always wears the skull of its dead mother, so no one has any idea what its hidden face looks like.

Pokemon.Name: Marowak
Pokemon.Description: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

Pokemon.Name: Hitmonlee
Pokemon.Description: If it starts kicking repeatedly, both legs will stretch even longer to strike a fleeing foe.

Pokemon.Name: Hitmonchan
Pokemon.Description: The spirit of a pro boxer has infused this Pokémon. It throws punches that are faster than a bullet train.

Pokemon.Name: Lickitung
Pokemon.Description: Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.

Pokemon.Name: Koffing
Pokemon.Description: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.

Pokemon.Name: Weezing
Pokemon.Description: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.

Pokemon.Name: Rhyhorn
Pokemon.Description: It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.

Pokemon.Name: Rhydon
Pokemon.Description: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

Pokemon.Name: Chansey
Pokemon.Description: It lays several eggs a day. The eggs are apparently rich in nutrients and extremely delicious.

Pokemon.Name: Tangela
Pokemon.Description: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.

Pokemon.Name: Kangaskhan
Pokemon.Description: If it is safe, the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.

Pokemon.Name: Horsea
Pokemon.Description: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

Pokemon.Name: Seadra
Pokemon.Description: It is capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its winglike pectoral fins and stout tail.

Pokemon.Name: Goldeen
Pokemon.Description: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the water dancer.

Pokemon.Name: Seaking
Pokemon.Description: It makes its nest by hollowing out boulders in streams with its horn. It defends its eggs with its life.

Pokemon.Name: Staryu
Pokemon.Description: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.

Pokemon.Name: Starmie
Pokemon.Description: At the centre of its body is a red core, which sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

Pokemon.Name: Mr. Mime
Pokemon.Description: It is adept at conning people. It is said to be able to create walls out of thin air by miming.

Pokemon.Name: Scyther
Pokemon.Description: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

Pokemon.Name: Jynx
Pokemon.Description: It speaks using a language that sounds human. Research is under way to determine what is being said.

Pokemon.Name: Electabuzz
Pokemon.Description: It loves to feed on strong electricity. It occasionally appears around large power plants and so on.

Pokemon.Name: Magmar
Pokemon.Description: Born in the spout of a volcano, its body is covered by flames that shimmer like the sun.

Pokemon.Name: Pinsir
Pokemon.Description: It swings its long pincer horns wildly to attack. During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.

Pokemon.Name: Tauros
Pokemon.Description: When it is about to tackle, it whips its body repeatedly with its three long tails.

Pokemon.Name: Magikarp
Pokemon.Description: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

Pokemon.Name: Gyarados
Pokemon.Description: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

Pokemon.Name: Lapras
Pokemon.Description: Its high intelligence enables it to understand human speech. It likes to ferry people on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Ditto
Pokemon.Description: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.

Pokemon.Name: Eevee
Pokemon.Description: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

Pokemon.Name: Vaporeon
Pokemon.Description: It has evolved to be suitable for an aquatic life. It can invisibly melt away into water.

Pokemon.Name: Jolteon
Pokemon.Description: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10,000-volt lightning bolts.

Pokemon.Name: Flareon
Pokemon.Description: It has a flame bag inside its body. After inhaling deeply, it blows out flames of nearly 1,648 degrees Celsius.

Pokemon.Name: Porygon
Pokemon.Description: A Pokémon that consists entirely of programming code. It is capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

Pokemon.Name: Omanyte
Pokemon.Description: Revived from an ancient fossil, this Pokémon uses air stored in its shell to sink and rise in water.

Pokemon.Name: Omastar
Pokemon.Description: Once wrapped around its prey, it never lets go. It eats the prey by tearing at it with sharp fangs.

Pokemon.Name: Kabuto
Pokemon.Description: This Pokémon was regenerated from the fossil of an ancient creature. It protects itself with a hard shell.

Pokemon.Name: Kabutops
Pokemon.Description: A slim and fast swimmer. It slices its prey with its sharp sickles and drinks the body fluids.

Pokemon.Name: Aerodactyl
Pokemon.Description: This vicious Pokémon is said to have flown in ancient skies while shrieking high-pitched cries.

Pokemon.Name: Snorlax
Pokemon.Description: Its stomach can digest any kind of food, even if it happens to be moldy or rotten.

Pokemon.Name: Articuno
Pokemon.Description: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

Pokemon.Name: Zapdos
Pokemon.Description: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

Pokemon.Name: Moltres
Pokemon.Description: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

Pokemon.Name: Dratini
Pokemon.Description: This Pokémon is full of life energy. It continually sheds its skin and grows steadily larger.

Pokemon.Name: Dragonair
Pokemon.Description: A mystical Pokémon that exudes a gentle aura. It is said to have the ability to change the weather.

Pokemon.Name: Dragonite
Pokemon.Description: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

Pokemon.Name: Mewtwo
Pokemon.Description: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

Pokemon.Name: Mew
Pokemon.Description: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.

Pokemon.Name: Chikorita
Pokemon.Description: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

Pokemon.Name: Bayleef
Pokemon.Description: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

Pokemon.Name: Meganium
Pokemon.Description: Meganium's breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

Pokemon.Name: Cyndaquil
Pokemon.Description: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.

Pokemon.Name: Quilava
Pokemon.Description: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Typhlosion
Pokemon.Description: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.

Pokemon.Name: Totodile
Pokemon.Description: Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.

Pokemon.Name: Croconaw
Pokemon.Description: Once it bites down, it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

Pokemon.Name: Feraligatr
Pokemon.Description: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

Pokemon.Name: Sentret
Pokemon.Description: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.

Pokemon.Name: Furret
Pokemon.Description: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.

Pokemon.Name: Hoothoot
Pokemon.Description: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

Pokemon.Name: Noctowl
Pokemon.Description: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

Pokemon.Name: Ledyba
Pokemon.Description: It is timid and clusters together with others. The fluid secreted by its feet indicates its location.

Pokemon.Name: Ledian
Pokemon.Description: The spot patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.

Pokemon.Name: Spinarak
Pokemon.Description: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

Pokemon.Name: Ariados
Pokemon.Description: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

Pokemon.Name: Crobat
Pokemon.Description: Having four wings allows it to fly more quickly and quietly so it can sneak up on prey without its noticing.

Pokemon.Name: Chinchou
Pokemon.Description: It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.

Pokemon.Name: Lanturn
Pokemon.Description: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light. With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon swallows it in a single gulp.

Pokemon.Name: Pichu
Pokemon.Description: It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.

Pokemon.Name: Cleffa
Pokemon.Description: Many appear when the night skies are filled with shooting stars. They disappear with sunrise.

Pokemon.Name: Igglybuff
Pokemon.Description: It has a very soft body. If it starts to roll, it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.

Pokemon.Name: Togepi
Pokemon.Description: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.

Pokemon.Name: Togetic
Pokemon.Description: They say that it will appear before kind hearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

Pokemon.Name: Natu
Pokemon.Description: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.

Pokemon.Name: Xatu
Pokemon.Description: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

Pokemon.Name: Mareep
Pokemon.Description: It stores lots of air in its soft fur, allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.

Pokemon.Name: Flaaffy
Pokemon.Description: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

Pokemon.Name: Ampharos
Pokemon.Description: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

Pokemon.Name: Bellossom
Pokemon.Description: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

Pokemon.Name: Marill
Pokemon.Description: The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.

Pokemon.Name: Azumarill
Pokemon.Description: The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it's in the water.

Pokemon.Name: Sudowoodo
Pokemon.Description: It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.

Pokemon.Name: Politoed
Pokemon.Description: If Poliwag and Poliwhirl hear its echoing cry, they respond by gathering from far and wide.

Pokemon.Name: Hoppip
Pokemon.Description: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

Pokemon.Name: Skiploom
Pokemon.Description: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.

Pokemon.Name: Jumpluff
Pokemon.Description: Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.

Pokemon.Name: Aipom
Pokemon.Description: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

Pokemon.Name: Sunkern
Pokemon.Description: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

Pokemon.Name: Sunflora
Pokemon.Description: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

Pokemon.Name: Yanma
Pokemon.Description: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

Pokemon.Name: Wooper
Pokemon.Description: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.

Pokemon.Name: Quagsire
Pokemon.Description: This carefree Pokémon has an easygoing nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.

Pokemon.Name: Espeon
Pokemon.Description: Its fur is so sensitive; it can feel minute shifts in the air and predict the weather...and its foes' thoughts.

Pokemon.Name: Umbreon
Pokemon.Description: When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it's filled with a mysterious power.

Pokemon.Name: Murkrow
Pokemon.Description: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

Pokemon.Name: Slowking
Pokemon.Description: When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke's head and unlocked an extraordinary power.

Pokemon.Name: Misdreavus
Pokemon.Description: It likes playing mischievous tricks, such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.

Pokemon.Name: Unown
Pokemon.Description: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

Pokemon.Name: Wobbuffet
Pokemon.Description: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

Pokemon.Name: Girafarig
Pokemon.Description: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.

Pokemon.Name: Pineco
Pokemon.Description: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

Pokemon.Name: Forretress
Pokemon.Description: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

Pokemon.Name: Dunsparce
Pokemon.Description: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.

Pokemon.Name: Gligar
Pokemon.Description: It flies straight at its target's face, and then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

Pokemon.Name: Steelix
Pokemon.Description: It chews its way through boulders with its sturdy jaws. Its eyes can see in the darkness underground.

Pokemon.Name: Snubbull
Pokemon.Description: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

Pokemon.Name: Granbull
Pokemon.Description: It can make most any Pokémon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.

Pokemon.Name: Qwilfish
Pokemon.Description: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.

Pokemon.Name: Scizor
Pokemon.Description: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.

Pokemon.Name: Shuckle
Pokemon.Description: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

Pokemon.Name: Heracross
Pokemon.Description: With its Herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

Pokemon.Name: Sneasel
Pokemon.Description: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

Pokemon.Name: Teddiursa
Pokemon.Description: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

Pokemon.Name: Ursaring
Pokemon.Description: Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.

Pokemon.Name: Slugma
Pokemon.Description: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

Pokemon.Name: Magcargo
Pokemon.Description: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.

Pokemon.Name: Swinub
Pokemon.Description: If it smells something enticing, it dashes off headlong to find the source of the aroma.

Pokemon.Name: Piloswine
Pokemon.Description: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.

Pokemon.Name: Corsola
Pokemon.Description: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their colour and deteriorate in dirty water.

Pokemon.Name: Remoraid
Pokemon.Description: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

Pokemon.Name: Octillery
Pokemon.Description: It traps foes with the suction cups on its tentacles, and then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

Pokemon.Name: Delibird
Pokemon.Description: It carries food all day long. When someone is lost in the mountains, it shares that food.

Pokemon.Name: Mantine
Pokemon.Description: While elegantly swimming in the sea, it ignores Remoraid that cling to its fins seeking food scraps.

Pokemon.Name: Skarmory
Pokemon.Description: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armour, it flies at speeds over 289 kph.

Pokemon.Name: Houndour
Pokemon.Description: To corner prey, they check each other's location using barks that only they can understand.

Pokemon.Name: Houndoom
Pokemon.Description: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

Pokemon.Name: Kingdra
Pokemon.Description: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life-forms can survive.

Pokemon.Name: Phanpy
Pokemon.Description: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Donphan
Pokemon.Description: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.

Pokemon.Name: Porygon2
Pokemon.Description: With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.

Pokemon.Name: Stantler
Pokemon.Description: The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.

Pokemon.Name: Smeargle
Pokemon.Description: Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrade's plant footprints on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Tyrogue
Pokemon.Description: To brush up on its fighting skills, it will challenge anyone. It has a very strong competitive spirit.

Pokemon.Name: Hitmontop
Pokemon.Description: If you are enchanted by its smooth, dance-like kicks, you may get a closer experience with one than you'd like.

Pokemon.Name: Smoochum
Pokemon.Description: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.

Pokemon.Name: Elekid
Pokemon.Description: Spinning its arms around to generate electricity makes the area between its horns shine light blue.

Pokemon.Name: Magby
Pokemon.Description: Its magma-like blood circulates throughout its body. Its body's heat can top 593 degrees Celsius.

Pokemon.Name: Miltank
Pokemon.Description: Its milk is packed with nutrition, making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.

Pokemon.Name: Blissey
Pokemon.Description: This kind hearted Pokémon nurses sick Pokémon to health. It senses feelings of sadness.

Pokemon.Name: Raikou
Pokemon.Description: This rough Pokémon stores energy inside its body, then sweeps across the land, shooting off electricity.

Pokemon.Name: Entei
Pokemon.Description: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

Pokemon.Name: Suicune
Pokemon.Description: Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

Pokemon.Name: Larvitar
Pokemon.Description: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

Pokemon.Name: Pupitar
Pokemon.Description: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.

Pokemon.Name: Tyranitar
Pokemon.Description: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.

Pokemon.Name: Lugia
Pokemon.Description: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumoured to have been seen on the night of a storm.

Pokemon.Name: Ho-Oh
Pokemon.Description: It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted Trainer by shining its bright, rainbow-coloured wings.

Pokemon.Name: Celebi
Pokemon.Description: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

Pokemon.Name: Treecko
Pokemon.Description: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

Pokemon.Name: Grovyle
Pokemon.Description: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

Pokemon.Name: Sceptile
Pokemon.Description: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.

Pokemon.Name: Torchic
Pokemon.Description: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 982 degrees Celsius.

Pokemon.Name: Combusken
Pokemon.Description: During a battle, the hot flame in its body increases. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

Pokemon.Name: Blaziken
Pokemon.Description: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.

Pokemon.Name: Mudkip
Pokemon.Description: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

Pokemon.Name: Marshtomp
Pokemon.Description: Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has made its legs sturdy.

Pokemon.Name: Swampert
Pokemon.Description: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.

Pokemon.Name: Poochyena
Pokemon.Description: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.

Pokemon.Name: Mightyena
Pokemon.Description: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

Pokemon.Name: Zigzagoon
Pokemon.Description: A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.

Pokemon.Name: Linoone
Pokemon.Description: It charges prey at speeds over 96 kph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

Pokemon.Name: Wurmple
Pokemon.Description: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by rising up the spikes on its rear.

Pokemon.Name: Silcoon
Pokemon.Description: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.

Pokemon.Name: Beautifly
Pokemon.Description: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.

Pokemon.Name: Cascoon
Pokemon.Description: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

Pokemon.Name: Dustox
Pokemon.Description: It violently flutters its wings to scatter toxic dust when attacked. It becomes active after sunset.

Pokemon.Name: Lotad
Pokemon.Description: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

Pokemon.Name: Lombre
Pokemon.Description: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.

Pokemon.Name: Ludicolo
Pokemon.Description: The rhythm of bright, festive music activates Ludicolo's cells, making it more powerful.

Pokemon.Name: Seedot
Pokemon.Description: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

Pokemon.Name: Nuzleaf
Pokemon.Description: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

Pokemon.Name: Shiftry
Pokemon.Description: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 30 m/s that can level houses.

Pokemon.Name: Taillow
Pokemon.Description: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 289 kph a day.

Pokemon.Name: Swellow
Pokemon.Description: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

Pokemon.Name: Wingull
Pokemon.Description: It makes its nest on steep sea cliffs. Riding updrafts, it soars to great heights.

Pokemon.Name: Pelipper
Pokemon.Description: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.

Pokemon.Name: Ralts
Pokemon.Description: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.

Pokemon.Name: Kirlia
Pokemon.Description: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

Pokemon.Name: Gardevoir
Pokemon.Description: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.

Pokemon.Name: Surskit
Pokemon.Description: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

Pokemon.Name: Masquerain
Pokemon.Description: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction--to and fro and sideways.

Pokemon.Name: Shroomish
Pokemon.Description: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

Pokemon.Name: Breloom
Pokemon.Description: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

Pokemon.Name: Slakoth
Pokemon.Description: If it eats just three leaves in a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20 hours a day.

Pokemon.Name: Vigoroth
Pokemon.Description: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

Pokemon.Name: Slaking
Pokemon.Description: It is the world's most slothful Pokémon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.

Pokemon.Name: Nincada
Pokemon.Description: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

Pokemon.Name: Ninjask
Pokemon.Description: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.

Pokemon.Name: Shedinja
Pokemon.Description: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.

Pokemon.Name: Whismur
Pokemon.Description: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.

Pokemon.Name: Loudred
Pokemon.Description: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.

Pokemon.Name: Exploud
Pokemon.Description: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor--or like an earthquake has struck.

Pokemon.Name: Makuhita
Pokemon.Description: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.

Pokemon.Name: Hariyama
Pokemon.Description: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

Pokemon.Name: Azurill
Pokemon.Description: It swings its large, nutrient-filled tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.

Pokemon.Name: Nosepass
Pokemon.Description: Its magnetic nose consistently faces north. Travellers check Nosepass to get their bearings.

Pokemon.Name: Skitty
Pokemon.Description: It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.

Pokemon.Name: Delcatty
Pokemon.Description: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.

Pokemon.Name: Sableye
Pokemon.Description: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

Pokemon.Name: Mawile
Pokemon.Description: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

Pokemon.Name: Aron
Pokemon.Description: When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.

Pokemon.Name: Lairon
Pokemon.Description: It habitually shows off its strength with the size of sparks it creates by ramming its steel body into boulders.

Pokemon.Name: Aggron
Pokemon.Description: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.

Pokemon.Name: Meditite
Pokemon.Description: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

Pokemon.Name: Medicham
Pokemon.Description: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

Pokemon.Name: Electrike
Pokemon.Description: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

Pokemon.Name: Manectric
Pokemon.Description: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

Pokemon.Name: Plusle
Pokemon.Description: It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.

Pokemon.Name: Minun
Pokemon.Description: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

Pokemon.Name: Volbeat
Pokemon.Description: It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.

Pokemon.Name: Illumise
Pokemon.Description: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

Pokemon.Name: Roselia
Pokemon.Description: Roselia that drink nutritionally rich spring water are said to reveal rare colouration when they bloom.

Pokemon.Name: Gulpin
Pokemon.Description: There is nothing its stomach can't digest. While it is digesting, vile, overpowering gases are expelled.

Pokemon.Name: Swalot
Pokemon.Description: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

Pokemon.Name: Carvanha
Pokemon.Description: It lives in massive rivers that course through jungles. It swarms prey that enters its territory.

Pokemon.Name: Sharpedo
Pokemon.Description: It can swim at speeds of 120 kph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.

Pokemon.Name: Wailmer
Pokemon.Description: It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out its blowholes with great force.

Pokemon.Name: Wailord
Pokemon.Description: The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

Pokemon.Name: Numel
Pokemon.Description: The magma in its body reaches 1,204 degrees Celsius. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.

Pokemon.Name: Camerupt
Pokemon.Description: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.

Pokemon.Name: Torkoal
Pokemon.Description: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

Pokemon.Name: Spoink
Pokemon.Description: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

Pokemon.Name: Grumpig
Pokemon.Description: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

Pokemon.Name: Spinda
Pokemon.Description: The chances of two Spinda having identical spot patterns is less than one in four billion.

Pokemon.Name: Trapinch
Pokemon.Description: It makes an inescapable conical pit and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

Pokemon.Name: Vibrava
Pokemon.Description: It generates ultrasonic waves by violently flapping its wings. After making its prey faint, it melts the prey with acid.

Pokemon.Name: Flygon
Pokemon.Description: Known as 'The Desert Spirit,' this Pokémon hides in the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.

Pokemon.Name: Cacnea
Pokemon.Description: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

Pokemon.Name: Cacturne
Pokemon.Description: Packs of them follow travellers through the desert until the travellers can no longer move.

Pokemon.Name: Swablu
Pokemon.Description: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.

Pokemon.Name: Altaria
Pokemon.Description: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.

Pokemon.Name: Zangoose
Pokemon.Description: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.

Pokemon.Name: Seviper
Pokemon.Description: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It's Zangoose's archrival.

Pokemon.Name: Lunatone
Pokemon.Description: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.

Pokemon.Name: Solrock
Pokemon.Description: It absorbs solar energy during the day. Always expressionless, it can sense what its foe is thinking.

Pokemon.Name: Barboach
Pokemon.Description: Its whiskers make superb radar. They are used to locate prey, even in the murkiest of water.

Pokemon.Name: Whiscash
Pokemon.Description: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything--if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

Pokemon.Name: Corphish
Pokemon.Description: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.

Pokemon.Name: Crawdaunt
Pokemon.Description: Loving to battle, this Pokémon pinches all Pokémon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.

Pokemon.Name: Baltoy
Pokemon.Description: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.

Pokemon.Name: Claydol
Pokemon.Description: It is said that it originates from clay dolls made by an ancient civilization.

Pokemon.Name: Lileep
Pokemon.Description: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.

Pokemon.Name: Cradily
Pokemon.Description: It ensnares prey with its eight tentacles. It then melts the prey with a strong acid before feeding.

Pokemon.Name: Anorith
Pokemon.Description: A Pokémon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.

Pokemon.Name: Armaldo
Pokemon.Description: Protected by a hard shell, its body is very sturdy. It skewers prey with its claws to feed.

Pokemon.Name: Feebas
Pokemon.Description: It is the shabbiest Pokémon of all. It forms in schools and lives at the bottom of rivers.

Pokemon.Name: Milotic
Pokemon.Description: It is the world's most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.

Pokemon.Name: Castform
Pokemon.Description: It has the ability to change its form into the sun, the rain, or a snow cloud, depending on the weather.

Pokemon.Name: Kecleon
Pokemon.Description: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.

Pokemon.Name: Shuppet
Pokemon.Description: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

Pokemon.Name: Banette
Pokemon.Description: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.

Pokemon.Name: Duskull
Pokemon.Description: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away--or so it's said.

Pokemon.Name: Dusclops
Pokemon.Description: Its body is hollow. It is said that those who look into its body are sucked into the void.

Pokemon.Name: Tropius
Pokemon.Description: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It's a highly favored tropical snack.

Pokemon.Name: Chimecho
Pokemon.Description: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

Pokemon.Name: Absol
Pokemon.Description: It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom bringer.

Pokemon.Name: Wynaut
Pokemon.Description: It grows strong by pushing up against others en masse. It loves eating sweet fruit.

Pokemon.Name: Snorunt
Pokemon.Description: In the snow country, certain folklore says a house will prosper if a Snorunt lives there.

Pokemon.Name: Glalie
Pokemon.Description: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.

Pokemon.Name: Spheal
Pokemon.Description: Its body is covered in fluffy fur. The fur keeps it from feeling cold while it is rolling on ice.

Pokemon.Name: Sealeo
Pokemon.Description: Be it Spheal or Poké Ball, it will spin any round object on its nose with the greatest of ease.

Pokemon.Name: Walrein
Pokemon.Description: It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.

Pokemon.Name: Clamperl
Pokemon.Description: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime, it makes a magnificent pearl.

Pokemon.Name: Huntail
Pokemon.Description: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

Pokemon.Name: Gorebyss
Pokemon.Description: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.

Pokemon.Name: Relicanth
Pokemon.Description: A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

Pokemon.Name: Luvdisc
Pokemon.Description: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.

Pokemon.Name: Bagon
Pokemon.Description: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

Pokemon.Name: Shelgon
Pokemon.Description: Its armoured body makes all attacks bounce off. The armour is too tough, however, making it heavy and somewhat sluggish.

Pokemon.Name: Salamence
Pokemon.Description: Its uncontrollable if enraged. It flies around spouting flames and scorching fields and mountains.

Pokemon.Name: Beldum
Pokemon.Description: It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.

Pokemon.Name: Metang
Pokemon.Description: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.

Pokemon.Name: Metagross
Pokemon.Description: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.

Pokemon.Name: Regirock
Pokemon.Description: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.

Pokemon.Name: Regice
Pokemon.Description: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of -200 degrees Celsius.

Pokemon.Name: Registeel
Pokemon.Description: Its body is said to be harder than any kind of metal. A study has revealed that its body is hollow.

Pokemon.Name: Latias
Pokemon.Description: It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.

Pokemon.Name: Latios
Pokemon.Description: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.

Pokemon.Name: Kyogre
Pokemon.Description: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

Pokemon.Name: Groudon
Pokemon.Description: This legendary Pokémon is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling Kyogre.

Pokemon.Name: Rayquaza
Pokemon.Description: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.

Pokemon.Name: Jirachi
Pokemon.Description: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

Pokemon.Name: Deoxys
Pokemon.Description: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.

Pokemon.Name: Turtwig
Pokemon.Description: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

Pokemon.Name: Grotle
Pokemon.Description: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Torterra
Pokemon.Description: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

Pokemon.Name: Chimchar
Pokemon.Description: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

Pokemon.Name: Monferno
Pokemon.Description: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

Pokemon.Name: Infernape
Pokemon.Description: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

Pokemon.Name: Piplup
Pokemon.Description: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

Pokemon.Name: Prinplup
Pokemon.Description: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

Pokemon.Name: Empoleon
Pokemon.Description: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

Pokemon.Name: Starly
Pokemon.Description: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

Pokemon.Name: Staravia
Pokemon.Description: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

Pokemon.Name: Staraptor
Pokemon.Description: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

Pokemon.Name: Bidoof
Pokemon.Description: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

Pokemon.Name: Bibarel
Pokemon.Description: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

Pokemon.Name: Kricketot
Pokemon.Description: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

Pokemon.Name: Kricketune
Pokemon.Description: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

Pokemon.Name: Shinx
Pokemon.Description: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

Pokemon.Name: Luxio
Pokemon.Description: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

Pokemon.Name: Luxray
Pokemon.Description: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

Pokemon.Name: Budew
Pokemon.Description: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

Pokemon.Name: Roserade
Pokemon.Description: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

Pokemon.Name: Cranidos
Pokemon.Description: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.

Pokemon.Name: Rampardos
Pokemon.Description: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

Pokemon.Name: Shieldon
Pokemon.Description: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

Pokemon.Name: Bastiodon
Pokemon.Description: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

Pokemon.Name: Burmy
Pokemon.Description: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

Pokemon.Name: Wormadam
Pokemon.Description: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

Pokemon.Name: Mothim
Pokemon.Description: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

Pokemon.Name: Combee
Pokemon.Description: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

Pokemon.Name: Vespiquen
Pokemon.Description: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

Pokemon.Name: Pachirisu
Pokemon.Description: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

Pokemon.Name: Buizel
Pokemon.Description: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

Pokemon.Name: Floatzel
Pokemon.Description: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

Pokemon.Name: Cherubi
Pokemon.Description: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

Pokemon.Name: Cherrim
Pokemon.Description: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.

Pokemon.Name: Shellos
Pokemon.Description: Its shape and colouration vary, depending on its habitat.

Pokemon.Name: Gastrodon
Pokemon.Description: It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.

Pokemon.Name: Ambipom
Pokemon.Description: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

Pokemon.Name: Drifloon
Pokemon.Description: These Pokémon are called the 'Signpost for Wandering Spirits.' Children holding them sometimes vanish.

Pokemon.Name: Drifblim
Pokemon.Description: It's drowsy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

Pokemon.Name: Buneary
Pokemon.Description: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

Pokemon.Name: Lopunny
Pokemon.Description: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.

Pokemon.Name: Mismagius
Pokemon.Description: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

Pokemon.Name: Honchkrow
Pokemon.Description: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.

Pokemon.Name: Glameow
Pokemon.Description: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

Pokemon.Name: Purugly
Pokemon.Description: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

Pokemon.Name: Chingling
Pokemon.Description: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

Pokemon.Name: Stunky
Pokemon.Description: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

Pokemon.Name: Skuntank
Pokemon.Description: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

Pokemon.Name: Bronzor
Pokemon.Description: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

Pokemon.Name: Bronzong
Pokemon.Description: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.

Pokemon.Name: Bonsly
Pokemon.Description: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.

Pokemon.Name: Mime Jr.
Pokemon.Description: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

Pokemon.Name: Happiny
Pokemon.Description: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It's bothered by how curly its hair looks.

Pokemon.Name: Chatot
Pokemon.Description: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

Pokemon.Name: Spiritomb
Pokemon.Description: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

Pokemon.Name: Gible
Pokemon.Description: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

Pokemon.Name: Gabite
Pokemon.Description: As it digs to expand its nest, it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.

Pokemon.Name: Garchomp
Pokemon.Description: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

Pokemon.Name: Munchlax
Pokemon.Description: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.

Pokemon.Name: Riolu
Pokemon.Description: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

Pokemon.Name: Lucario
Pokemon.Description: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

Pokemon.Name: Hippopotas
Pokemon.Description: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

Pokemon.Name: Hippowdon
Pokemon.Description: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

Pokemon.Name: Skorupi
Pokemon.Description: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.

Pokemon.Name: Drapion
Pokemon.Description: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

Pokemon.Name: Croagunk
Pokemon.Description: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

Pokemon.Name: Toxicroak
Pokemon.Description: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

Pokemon.Name: Carnivine
Pokemon.Description: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

Pokemon.Name: Finneon
Pokemon.Description: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

Pokemon.Name: Lumineon
Pokemon.Description: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.

Pokemon.Name: Mantyke
Pokemon.Description: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean, people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Snover
Pokemon.Description: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

Pokemon.Name: Abomasnow
Pokemon.Description: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

Pokemon.Name: Weavile
Pokemon.Description: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

Pokemon.Name: Magnezone
Pokemon.Description: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

Pokemon.Name: Lickilicky
Pokemon.Description: Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.

Pokemon.Name: Rhyperior
Pokemon.Description: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

Pokemon.Name: Tangrowth
Pokemon.Description: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.

Pokemon.Name: Electivire
Pokemon.Description: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

Pokemon.Name: Magmortar
Pokemon.Description: It blasts fireballs of over 1,982 degrees Celsius out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.

Pokemon.Name: Togekiss
Pokemon.Description: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

Pokemon.Name: Yanmega
Pokemon.Description: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

Pokemon.Name: Leafeon
Pokemon.Description: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

Pokemon.Name: Glaceon
Pokemon.Description: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

Pokemon.Name: Gliscor
Pokemon.Description: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

Pokemon.Name: Mamoswine
Pokemon.Description: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

Pokemon.Name: Porygon-Z
Pokemon.Description: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

Pokemon.Name: Gallade
Pokemon.Description: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

Pokemon.Name: Probopass
Pokemon.Description: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

Pokemon.Name: Dusknoir
Pokemon.Description: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

Pokemon.Name: Froslass
Pokemon.Description: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as Froslass.

Pokemon.Name: Rotom
Pokemon.Description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

Pokemon.Name: Uxie
Pokemon.Description: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.

Pokemon.Name: Mesprit
Pokemon.Description: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.

Pokemon.Name: Azelf
Pokemon.Description: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

Pokemon.Name: Dialga
Pokemon.Description: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

Pokemon.Name: Palkia
Pokemon.Description: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

Pokemon.Name: Heatran
Pokemon.Description: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

Pokemon.Name: Regigigas
Pokemon.Description: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

Pokemon.Name: Giratina
Pokemon.Description: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

Pokemon.Name: Cresselia
Pokemon.Description: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

Pokemon.Name: Phione
Pokemon.Description: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

Pokemon.Name: Manaphy
Pokemon.Description: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

Pokemon.Name: Darkrai
Pokemon.Description: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

Pokemon.Name: Shaymin
Pokemon.Description: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

Pokemon.Name: Arceus
Pokemon.Description: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

Pokemon.Name: Victini
Pokemon.Description: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.

Pokemon.Name: Snivy
Pokemon.Description: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

Pokemon.Name: Servine
Pokemon.Description: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

Pokemon.Name: Serperior
Pokemon.Description: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

Pokemon.Name: Tepig
Pokemon.Description: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

Pokemon.Name: Pignite
Pokemon.Description: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

Pokemon.Name: Emboar
Pokemon.Description: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

Pokemon.Name: Oshawott
Pokemon.Description: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

Pokemon.Name: Dewott
Pokemon.Description: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

Pokemon.Name: Samurott
Pokemon.Description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

Pokemon.Name: Patrat
Pokemon.Description: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.

Pokemon.Name: Watchog
Pokemon.Description: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

Pokemon.Name: Lillipup
Pokemon.Description: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it's also smart enough to check its foe's strength and avoid battle.

Pokemon.Name: Herdier
Pokemon.Description: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

Pokemon.Name: Stoutland
Pokemon.Description: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.

Pokemon.Name: Purrloin
Pokemon.Description: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

Pokemon.Name: Liepard
Pokemon.Description: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

Pokemon.Name: Pansage
Pokemon.Description: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

Pokemon.Name: Simisage
Pokemon.Description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

Pokemon.Name: Pansear
Pokemon.Description: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 315 degrees Celsius.

Pokemon.Name: Simisear
Pokemon.Description: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

Pokemon.Name: Panpour
Pokemon.Description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

Pokemon.Name: Simipour
Pokemon.Description: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

Pokemon.Name: Munna
Pokemon.Description: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-coloured mist.

Pokemon.Name: Musharna
Pokemon.Description: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colours depending on the dream that was eaten.

Pokemon.Name: Pidove
Pokemon.Description: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

Pokemon.Name: Tranquill
Pokemon.Description: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

Pokemon.Name: Unfezant
Pokemon.Description: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

Pokemon.Name: Blitzle
Pokemon.Description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

Pokemon.Name: Zebstrika
Pokemon.Description: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

Pokemon.Name: Roggenrola
Pokemon.Description: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

Pokemon.Name: Boldore
Pokemon.Description: When it is healthy, its core sticks out. Always facing the same way, it swiftly moves front to back and left to right.

Pokemon.Name: Gigalith
Pokemon.Description: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

Pokemon.Name: Woobat
Pokemon.Description: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

Pokemon.Name: Swoobat
Pokemon.Description: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

Pokemon.Name: Drilbur
Pokemon.Description: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 48 kph.

Pokemon.Name: Excadrill
Pokemon.Description: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

Pokemon.Name: Audino
Pokemon.Description: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

Pokemon.Name: Timburr
Pokemon.Description: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.

Pokemon.Name: Gurdurr
Pokemon.Description: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

Pokemon.Name: Conkeldurr
Pokemon.Description: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.

Pokemon.Name: Tympole
Pokemon.Description: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

Pokemon.Name: Palpitoad
Pokemon.Description: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.

Pokemon.Name: Seismitoad
Pokemon.Description: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

Pokemon.Name: Throh
Pokemon.Description: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

Pokemon.Name: Sawk
Pokemon.Description: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

Pokemon.Name: Sewaddle
Pokemon.Description: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

Pokemon.Name: Swadloon
Pokemon.Description: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

Pokemon.Name: Leavanny
Pokemon.Description: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

Pokemon.Name: Venipede
Pokemon.Description: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

Pokemon.Name: Whirlipede
Pokemon.Description: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

Pokemon.Name: Scolipede
Pokemon.Description: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

Pokemon.Name: Cottonee
Pokemon.Description: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.

Pokemon.Name: Whimsicott
Pokemon.Description: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

Pokemon.Name: Petilil
Pokemon.Description: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

Pokemon.Name: Lilligant
Pokemon.Description: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

Pokemon.Name: Basculin
Pokemon.Description: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's school.

Pokemon.Name: Sandile
Pokemon.Description: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

Pokemon.Name: Krokorok
Pokemon.Description: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness.

Pokemon.Name: Krookodile
Pokemon.Description: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

Pokemon.Name: Darumaka
Pokemon.Description: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 593 degrees Celsius.

Pokemon.Name: Darmanitan
Pokemon.Description: Its internal fire burns at 1,371 degrees Celsius, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

Pokemon.Name: Maractus
Pokemon.Description: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

Pokemon.Name: Dwebble
Pokemon.Description: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

Pokemon.Name: Crustle
Pokemon.Description: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

Pokemon.Name: Scraggy
Pokemon.Description: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.

Pokemon.Name: Scrafty
